    "pfs": "Standard",
    "aonid": 2661,
    "game-obj": "Equipment",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "The geometric designs of this warding tattoo extend the length of your arm, resembling an armored sleeve. The crimson ink sometimes glows softly like warm coals when you're excited or building something new.  \n **Forming the Bond** Defeat Tuom Molgrade and befriend her tattoo guardian with Clan Molgrade's blessing.  \n **Advancing the Bond** Create extraordinary objects that earn renown. Protect innocents and your companions despite great personal risk.  \n **Minor Gifts** create spark, obscure, shadow smith   \n **Major Gifts** dancing shadow, elements of creation; dancing shadow Strikes use the relic's spell attack modifier.",
        "level": 5,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Unique",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 161,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "a179d6a05b0c814096f81ec4373a54f6",
                "text": "A rules element with this trait is one-of-a-kind. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to creatures with this trait is increased by 10.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "unique"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Conjuration",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 630,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9011037bb4a11ca6cf2d16fa8a657bf5",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the conjuration school of magic, typically involving summoning, creation, teleportation, or moving things from place to place.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "summoning",
                        "alt": "summoning",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 154
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "teleportation",
                        "alt": "teleportation",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 156
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Relic",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Treasure Vault",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Treasure Vault pg. 201",
                            "alt": "Treasure Vault pg. 201",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        },
                        "page": 201,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "bfe92d4381df632cdf5a15b8e135154a",
                "text": "Nethys note: this trait has not been defined, but has been used for relic seeds and set relics.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "relic seeds",
                        "alt": "relic seeds",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 1096
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "set relics",
                        "alt": "set relics",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 1970
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Shadow",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 143,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 460,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "83242b57548e68270396486e2a540b6b",
                "text": "Magic with this trait involves shadows or the energy of the Netherworld.  \n  \n Planes with this trait are umbral with murky light. In the Netherworld, the radius of all light from light sources and the areas of light spells are halved.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Tattoo",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Secrets of Magic",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Secrets of Magic pg. 164",
                            "alt": "Secrets of Magic pg. 164",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 96
                        },
                        "page": 164,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 96
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "ef22b9fe943cfd5f67438e0d926a6979",
                "text": "A magical tattoo has the tattoo trait. It's permanently a part of the subject's body, and reduces the number of items that creature can invest per day by 1. Each tattoo has the invested trait to indicate this limitation\u2014a magical tattoo is like an invested item that the tattooed creature has no choice but to invest. If the tattoo loses its magic or is destroyed, it no longer reduces your investiture.  \n  \n Just like a physical magic item, a magical tattoo can be counteracted by spells like _dispel magic_ or _disjunction_. If destroyed, the tattoo fades from the skin.  \n  \n If a creature gets a new magical tattoo when their limit on invested items has already been reduced to zero, the new tattoo's magic fails to take hold, and it becomes a non-magical tattoo instead. However, a tattooist can alter an existing tattoo when they Craft a tattoo, modifying the old one into a different magical tattoo and removing the old effect. Magical tattoos can usually be upgraded into their greater versions by having a tattooist add to or modify the existing tattoo.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invested",
                        "alt": "invested",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "dispel magic",
                        "alt": "dispel magic",
                        "game-obj": "Spells",
                        "aonid": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "disjunction",
                        "alt": "disjunction",
                        "game-obj": "Spells",
                        "aonid": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "upgraded into their greater versions",
                        "alt": "upgraded into their greater versions",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 701
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
